criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient aged over 18 years with cancer and palliative hospital situation

          -  Patient able to communicate with the nursing staff;

          -  Patient able to understand the meaning of the questions;

          -  Patients whose length of stay is at least 5 days

          -  Patients whose life expectancy is greater than or equal to three weeks;

          -  Patients who have given their written consent to the study participation.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient refusing to make the clinical assessment;

          -  Patient not giving their consent for participation;

          -  Patient unable to communicate with the nursing staff;

          -  Patient not proficient in the French language;

          -  Patient suffering from cognitive deficits.
